<P>
REQUEST CRITICIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Planned Parenthood has asked the City Council of Santa Maria for $60,000 in 
Housing and Urban Development (HUD) funds. 
</P>
<P>
Planned Parenthood claims that it needs the money to help poor women. Why does 
it want to use HUD money? Is it right to take the funds provided for affordable 
housing for families and senior citizens, just so Planned Parenthood can 
continue the slaughter of 28 million unborn children? Are they really concerned 
about the poor? Planned Parenthood is the leading provider of abortion in the 
nation and the world. 
</P>
