<P>
MARIE LOUISE SOLER; LONGTIME CANOGA PARK RESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marie Louise Soler, whose family ranch became a large part of Canoga Park, has 
died in West Hills. She was 86. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Soler died Saturday of cancer, said her son, Joseph Soler. 
</P>
<P>
Born Marie Louise Davancaze on June 6, 1904, in Bordeaux, France, she came to 
the United States in 1920 and married Manuel Soler in the early 1920s. She 
raised a family on a 200-acre ranch in Canoga Park -- then called Owensmouth -- 
until the family started selling the property in the late 1950s. She lived in 
the area for the rest of her life. 
</P>
<P>
She is survived by her son, Joseph Soler of West Hills; six grandchildren and 
eight great-grandchildren. Her husband died in 1977. 
</P>
<P>
Visitation is planned from 5 to 8:30 p.m. Wednesday and a rosary will be 
recited at 7:30 p.m., both at Pierce Brothers Praiswater Mortuary, 7245 Remmet 
Ave., in Canoga Park which is handling the arrangements. A funeral Mass is 
scheduled for 9 a.m. Thursday at Our Lady of the Valley Catholic Church, 7117 
Topanga Canyon Blvd., in Canoga Park with burial to follow at Holy Cross 
Cemetery in Culver City. 
</P>
