<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGRY OVER 'VISITORS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Baby Boom Pushes a Hospital to Limit": 
</P>
<P>
I feel that our public maternity wards are being abused by "visitors" from 
other countries. Last year, a relative of a friend came to Los Angeles under 
the presumption of visiting a family member. 
</P>
<P>
This man and his wife arrived in L.A. approximately two weeks before her due 
date. 
</P>
<P>
The woman had not received proper prenatal care in her native country. She was 
also in need of Medi-Cal assistance to defray the cost of her maternity stay. 
Somehow, the proper paperwork was completed and this young lady delivered her 
baby boy by C-section at Olive View Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
What really angered me was the fact that these so-called "visitors" returned to 
their country about three weeks after the birth of their son. 
</P>
<P>
Why are we, the taxpayers, left with these outrageous bills? We can't even take 
care of our own Medi-Cal patients, but we are willing to pay for outsiders to 
deliver their babies in American hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
We should seriously investigate why we taxpayers are paying for these births 
and supporting these visitors. 
</P>
<P>
CAROLE RODIN 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 
</P>
</TEXT>
