<P>
The wife of Charles H. Keating Jr. says his three weeks in the Los Angeles 
County Jail have been a "living nightmare" as he awaits trial on securities 
fraud charges stemming from his time as chairman of American Continental Corp., 
former parent of the failed Lincoln Savings &amp; Loan. 
</P>
