<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 3.1 QUAKE STRIKES 9 MILES SOUTH OF MALIBU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An earthquake measuring magnitude 3.1 occurred at 9:02 p.m. Monday in the 
ocean, nine miles south of Malibu, officials at the Caltech Seismology Lab in 
Pasasdena reported. 
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of damage or injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The sheriff's Malibu station got a few calls about the quake, said Sgt. Linda 
Spradin. 
</P>
<P>
"I felt it myself personally," Spradin said. "It was two small, almost 
imperceptible rollers. Very quick." 
</P>
