<P>
RAM NUMBERS 
</P>
<P>
HIGHLIGHT: BOOMER ESIASON 
</P>
<P>
He wasn't exactly a complete stranger to either the Rams or their fans -- they 
had watched some of his magic on television since 1985 -- but Boomer showed 
Sunday's Anaheim Stadium crowd conclusively why he was the AFC's top-rated 
quarterback the last two seasons. The Bengal left-hander completed 30 of 40 
passes for a club record 471 yards in his team's 34-31, overtime win. Not even 
nemesis Joe Montana of the 49ers has ever thrown for that many yards against 
the Rams -- his best being 458 yards last December. It was Esiason's third 
400-plus-yard performance as a pro. 
</P>
