<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
USC; 
</P>
<P>
ROYSTER, LOCKWOOD JOIN FAST COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When was the last time USC had a 200-yard rusher and a 100-yard rusher in the 
same game, as it did Saturday night against Washington State, when tailback 
Mazio Royster ran for 203 yards in 34 carries and fullback Scott Lockwood ran 
for 102 yards in 20 carries? 
</P>
<P>
It hasn't happened since 1929, when Russ Saunders ran for 234 yards, Jess Hill 
ran for 166 and USC piled up 753 yards on the ground in the first USC-UCLA 
game. 
</P>
<P>
USC won, 76-0. Its rushing yardage is still a conference record. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Todd Marinovich hasn't thrown a touchdown pass since Sept. 15, when 
he passed five yards to tight end Frank Griffin with 3:05 left in the first 
quarter of a 19-14 victory over Penn State. That's 15 quarters without a 
touchdown pass for Marinovich, who threw three in USC's opener against Syracuse 
but has only one since. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
UNIVERSITY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; FOOTBALL PLAYERS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
