<HEADLINE>
<P>
HE WASN'T BUCKWHEAT, '20-20' ACKNOWLEDGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'It was a real foul-up in research," a spokeswoman for "20/20" acknowledged 
Monday, referring to the ABC program's story last Friday about a grocery clerk 
in Tempe, Ariz., who it said used to star as Buckwheat in the "Our Gang" 
comedies. 
</P>
<P>
The actor who actually played the role, William Thomas, died in 1980. 
</P>
<P>
"20/20" spokeswoman Maurie Pearl said that the magazine show had undertaken the 
segment after receiving a letter from a viewer who said that the man who had 
played Buckwheat in the films of the 1930s and '40s was living in Tempe. The 
man interviewed was named Bill English; he told "20/20" that he had changed his 
last name from Thomas. 
</P>
<P>
The network is looking into the matter and is likely to apologize when "20/20" 
airs Friday, Pearl said. Whatever disciplinary action is taken will be handled 
internally, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
20 20 (TELEVISION PROGRAM); RESEARCH; MISTAKES; ACTORS; MISTAKEN IDENTITY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
