<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PINKERTON'S 3RD-QUARTER PROFIT UP 61% FROM 1989 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pinkerton's Inc., a Van Nuys-based security services concern, said its fiscal 
third-quarter profit soared 61% from a year earlier despite a 4% decline in 
revenue. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter ended Sept. 7, Pinkerton's said its net income jumped to $2.79 
million from $1.73 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Its revenue slipped to $135.5 million from $140.6 million, which the company 
said reflected its decision to drop some marginal clients. 
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months of its fiscal year, Pinkerton's profit was $2.99 
million, down from $3.73 million a year earlier. The lower earnings were due to 
a one-time, $2.8-million charge in the latest period stemming from Pinkerton's 
early repayment of debt. Its nine-month revenue fell 4% to $403.1 million from 
$419.6 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
