<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: BANK OF A. LEVY BUYS MIDWEST SAVINGS DEPOSITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bank of A. Levy in Ventura said it bought the deposits of Midwest Savings 
Assn.'s two offices in Fillmore and Orange County for $725,000. 
</P>
<P>
The bank bought the $58 million of deposits from the Resolution Trust Corp., 
the federal agency that is liquidating insolvent savings and loan associations. 
Midwest Savings is based in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
Bank of A. Levy, with $680 million in total assets, has 21 branch offices 
including one in Fillmore. The 108-year-old bank previously has said it will 
pursue acquisitions to increase its growth. 
</P>
