<HEADLINE>
<P>
KNIFE-WIELDING BLACKS STAB 9 WHITES NEAR S. AFRICA BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DURBAN, South Africa 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group of blacks stole knives from a store and went on a rampage today, 
stabbing nine whites on a busy street near the beachfront of this Indian Ocean 
city, witnesses and officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they had no motive for the attack, which seriously injured six of 
the victims. 
</P>
<P>
Despite deep racial divisions and widespread violence in South Africa, there 
have been few cases of blacks randomly attacking whites. 
</P>
<P>
About 5,000 blacks have been killed in factional fighting since 1986 in Natal 
province, which includes Durban. But the violence has been almost exclusively 
in black areas. 
</P>
<P>
Patrick Lekota, a spokesman for the African National Congress, said the attack 
"was a desperate attempt to discredit the liberation movement as a whole." 
</P>
<P>
"They were in a berserk state and were lashing out with knives at anyone who 
was near them," witness Robert Trulock told the independent South African Press 
Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Five suspects were arrested, including two who were shot and wounded by police, 
the report said. 
</P>
<P>
The gang of between 10 and 20 young men took the knives from a store 
specializing in weapons from the Far East, police said. The men then ran down a 
street next to the beachfront, assaulting whites at random, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
Bleeding victims staggered into the lobby of the Lonsdale Hotel and collapsed 
in front of horrified guests. 
</P>
<P>
Nine whites suffered stab wounds and were admitted to nearby Addington 
Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
