<P>
PORTLAND SOCCER TEAM FOR SALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PORTLAND, Ore. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The financially troubled Portland Timbers professional soccer team is up for 
sale. 
</P>
<P>
Art Dixon, the team's majority owner, said the Timbers have lost about $600,000 
during his two-year tenure. Current debts include about $10,000 owed to coaches 
and players in back salaries. 
</P>
<P>
Dixon said if new investors or owners are not found by Nov. 1, the team would 
fold. 
</P>
<P>
The Timbers are in the Western Division of the American Professional Soccer 
League. 
</P>
<P>
Dixon said most of the financial losses occurred this past season, when the 
team suffered from poor home attendance and failed to qualify for the 
divisional playoffs. Attendance averaged 3,149 per game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
